{<b>Oh, how blessed, how beloved thou art!</b>}
]

[
{<color=#6B0000>Thy apostles kneel upon the sky and lift their prayers unto thee, who liest now upon the earth. Thy blood floweth freely from thy wounds, climbing upward along the beams of the cross toward the heavens. Tears creep across thy brow. The joyous angels dance upon the edge of thy mind—or is it but a vision wrought by the loss of thy blood? Thou wouldst tell thy disciples of the joy within thee, yet thy lips shall never part again. But what doth it matter? To the most joyful soul in all the world, what need is there for words?</color>}
]

